article.headline: Quinnipiac 73, Dartmouth 51
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. -- James Feldeine scored 18 points and Jeremy Baker added 15 to lead Quinnipiac to a 73-51 victory over Dartmouth on Wednesday. Justin Rutty and Jamee Jackson each chipped in with 10 points for the Bobcats (6-5), who led 34-21 at halftime and had a 42-22 rebounding edge in the game. Matt LaBove scored 13 points to lead Dartmouth (2-10), which hit only 19 of its 50 field goal attempts.
